      "text": "## Analysis Results\n\n### (1) Full Path\n\u0060/Users/pgermishuys/source/opencode-debug/Program.cs\u0060\n\n### (2) Concise Summary\nThis is an **OpenCode Debug Inspector** \u2014 a diagnostic CLI tool that:\n- Spawns an \u0060opencode serve\u0060 process on a dynamically-assigned port\n- Authenticates with Basic Auth (random password)\n- Creates a session for a specified working directory\n- Subscribes to Server-Sent Events (SSE) to monitor all server events in real-time\n- Provides an interactive prompt loop to send prompts to the OpenCode server\n- Logs all activity (console \u002B timestamped file) with color-coded output for different event types\n\n### (3) Notable Startup/Configuration Patterns \u0026 Risks\n\n**Patterns:**\n- \u2705 **Graceful process lifecycle**: Spawns subprocess, monitors stdout/stderr, handles exit events\n- \u2705 **Timeout protection**: 30-second timeout waiting for server readiness\n- \u2705 **Thread-safe logging**: Uses \u0060lock(consoleLock)\u0060 for concurrent console writes\n- \u2705 **Cancellation support**: Integrates \u0060CancellationTokenSource\u0060 for Ctrl\u002BC handling\n- \u2705 **Dynamic port discovery**: Uses regex to parse server URL from stdout\n- \u2705 **Synchronized file logging**: Timestamped log file with UTF-8 encoding\n\n**Risks \u0026 Concerns:**\n1. **\u26A0\uFE0F Bare \u0060catch\u0060 blocks** (lines 155, 227, 297): Silently swallow exceptions without logging details \u2014 could hide startup failures\n2. **\u26A0\uFE0F No validation of \u0060opencode\u0060 command**: Assumes \u0060opencode\u0060 is on PATH; failure message only appears after timeout\n3. **\u26A0\uFE0F Fire-and-forget SSE task** (line 185): Background task runs without awaiting; exceptions logged but not propagated\n4. **\u26A0\uFE0F Hardcoded credentials**: Username \u0022debug\u0022 \u002B random GUID password passed via environment variables \u2014 acceptable for debug tool but not production-safe\n5. **\u26A0\uFE0F No retry logic**: Single attempt to create session; network hiccup = failure\n6. **\u26A0\uFE0F Process cleanup race condition** (line 294): \u0060Kill()\u0060 called without checking if process already exited\n7. **\u26A0\uFE0F Unhandled JSON parsing**: Line 176 assumes session response has \u0022id\u0022 property; no null/missing property handling",
